50|$|Lisburn is {{also known}} as the birthplace of Ireland's linen industry, which was {{established}} in 1698 by Louis Crommelin and other Huguenots. An exhibition about <b>the</b> Irish <b>linen</b> industry is now housed in <b>the</b> Irish <b>Linen</b> Centre, which {{can be found in the}} old Market House in Market Square.|$|R
